<dl id="n36037b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36037b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36037b"> 37(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> deff</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">James Donaldson (1751-1830) was a printer who bequeathed nearly the whole of his large fortune for the purposes of a hospital for poor boys and girls, and the trustees have usually selected half of the children admitted from the ranks of <mark>the deaf</mark> and dumb. <small> &ldquo;EDINBURGH&rdquo; <a name="EBED" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBED"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 942n2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
